Definition: an almond-shaped neural structure in the anterior part of the temporal lobe of the cerebrum
Example: intimately connected with the hypothalamus and the hippocampus and the cingulate gyrus; as part of the limbic system it plays an important role in motivation and emotional behavior
Synonyms: amygdaloid_nucleus, corpus_amygdaloideum, basal_ganglion, limbic_system, p, temporal_lobe, an, almond-shaped, neural, structure, in, the, anterior, part, of, temporal, lobe, cerebrum, intimately, connected, with, hypothalamus, and, hippocampus, cingulate, gyrus, as, limbic, system, it, plays, important, role, motivation, emotional, behavior
Category: noun.body
